The paper focuses on the development of active haptic exploration strategies using robotic hands, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed approach involves Bayesian models for touch attention mechanisms, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The models integrate compliance and texture features extracted from haptic sensory data, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV). The models also use saliency and uncertainty maps, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the models are used to make motor decisions based on haptic percepts, which suggests a focus on control systems (cs.SY).
